# [Server-Side-Vulnerability] — [Username enumeration via different responses]

## Summary

 This lab is vulnerable to username enumeration and password brute-force attacks. It has an account with a predictable username and password, which can be found in the following wordlists:

    Candidate usernames
    Candidate passwords

To solve the lab, enumerate a valid username, brute-force this user's password, then access their account page.

**Fix**
1. Make sure you are intercepting the page via burpsuite in Portswigger
2. enter a demo credential to obtain the POST method on login page
3. Go to burpsuite
4. Send that request to the intruder
5. Inside intruder clear all auto set markers and only select the username field
6. Select attack type to sniper
7. In payload type enter the usernames list 
8. Start Attack
9. After the attack is complete see the length column most of them are identical but for the right response the length field may give different output
10. Repeat again the same, this time with password field and make sure to enter the right username you got from previous attack
11. Enter the credentials and login

